decision_conditions:
CONDITION: Detailed drawings of the following shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of the relevant part of the works and shall be installed in accordance with those details approved and maintained thereafter:

1)	Plan, elevation and sections of components (scale 1:5) of the proposed new handrails to the Northampton Square entrance;
2)	Plan, elevation and sections (scale 1:5 with railing detail at 1:1) of the existing railings adapted to form the lift gate at the Wycliff Street entrance;
3)	Plan and section (scale 1:10) of rebuilt steps with materials annotated.

REASON: To ensure that the Local Planning Authority may be satisfied with the external appearance of the building and in accordance with policies 7.4 and 7.8 of the London Plan 2011, policies CS8 (Enhancing Islington’s Character) and CS9 (Protecting and Enhancing Islington’s Built and Historic Environment) of Islington’s Core Strategy 2011, policies D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and extensions), D24 (Materials), of Islington's Unitary Development Plan 2002, , policies DM1 (Design), DM3 (Heritage) of Islington’s Development Management Policies Submission Version 2012, Islington's Urban Design Guide (2006) and the Northampton Square Conservation Area Design Guidelines, and the NPPF 2012.
